SSH Debug
---------

To perform SSH debugging on the Chipsee Raspberry |Pi| product, you must first connect the product to the Internet.

Continue the debugging by follow these steps:

* Get the IP address of the Chipsee Raspberry |Pi| product.
* Enable the SSH feature in the Chipsee Raspberry |Pi| product by running the following command in debug console:
    .. code:: bash

        $ sudo raspi-config

        Interfacing Options -> SSH -> Yes

* If you donâ€™t have a debug console, you can also use the GUI feature to enable SSH.
    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/SSH_Debug.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/SSH_Debug_2.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       Enabling SSH (GUI)

* Open and configure XShell or use ssh tool in the PC directly
* In XShell, add a new session and set it as shown in the figure below.
    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/SSH_Debug_3.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       SSH Setting on Xshell

* Now we can perform SSH debugging using XShell
    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/SSH_Debug_4.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       SSH Debug
